Eskom has also warned there’s a risk of outages until the middle of next week as the utility battles capacity constraints. JOHANNESBURG - South Africans can expect stage 2 load shedding to last until at least Sunday. Eskom has also warned there’s a risk of outages until the middle of next week as the utility battles capacity constraints. Stage two load shedding kicked in at 8 am on Friday morning; it’s expected to last until about 11 pm. More to follow.